cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification using unsupervised learning methods. The approach proposed in the paper is based on hierarchical clustering, which is a common technique used in computer vision and machine learning for clustering and segmentation tasks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new distance measurement strategy and regularization term to improve the clustering performance, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on large-scale datasets, which involves data management and processing techniques, and may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
